analysis_commentary: The group of carers who had the lowest proportion of positive responses when asked about the ease of finding information were those aged 25 to 34 in both years of the survey. For groups older than 25 to 34, the proportion who reported finding it easy to find information increases with age.
data_source: Health & Social Care Information Centre,  Personal Social Services Survey of Adult Carers in England
